\end_layout

\end_inset

, by the conserved CXXC motif, where C corresponds to a cysteine residue,
 and X corresponds to any of 20 canonical amino acids.
 The Zn(II) co-coordination of the cysteine's thiolates implies that Zn(II)
 directly takes part in the formation of the tertiary structure of the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{rad}
\end_layout

\end_inset

