literal "false"

\end_inset

).
 However,  the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{UniProt}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 marks 
\emph on
a priori
\emph default
 the stretch of around 100 amino acids flanking the canonical CXXC motif
 to be the zinc hook, however,  this approach seems to be experimentally
 unjustified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In structural biology, protein domain is understood as a part of the protein
 that is folded independently of the rest of the protein, and is stable
 
\emph on
per se
\emph default
.
 Combining this with the 
\emph on
a priori
\emph default
 assignment of the zinc hook domain is not justified in the lack of the
 structural discriminant of the coiled coil and the zinc hook domain.
 The marking of the region that makes the zinc hook domain should be 
\emph on
functional 
\emph default
(e.g.
 assessment of the stability), not structural.
 This distinction is possible due to the experimental work performed by
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citeauthor
key "Kochanczyk2016"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 and complemented further by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citeauthor
key "Padjasek2020a"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 for the zinc hook domain from 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{pf}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{rad}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Kochanczyk2016,Kochanczyk2016a,Padjasek2020a"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 The stabilities studies show that in the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{rad}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{pf}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 only a 45-amino-acid-long fragment (with the CXXC motif and flanking region)
 is sufficient to form a stable domain, further elongation does not result
 in the stabilization, thus the zinc hook in the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{UniProt}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 should be annotated as this short region in case of 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{pf}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The stabilities studies performed during my PhD project show that in the
 case of the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{hs}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{rad}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 the zinc hook domain is longer—an increment in the stability of the zinc
 hook domain is observed up to a length of ~130 amino acids (see 
\begin_inset Flex CT - auto cross-reference
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand labelonly
reference "chap:hRad50"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

).
 
